{{Italic title}}
'''''San Francisco Estuary and Watershed Science''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[open access]] [[scientific journal]] covering research about the science and resource management of [[San Francisco Bay]], the [[Sacramento–San Joaquin River Delta]], and the upstream watersheds. The journal was established in October 2003 and is published jointly by the John Muir Institute of the Environment ([[University of California, Davis]]) and the [[Delta Stewardship Council]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] is Samuel N. Luoma (University of California, Davis).

==Abstracting and indexing==
The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[Scopus]]<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref> and [[The Zoological Record]].<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref>

